1027
1:28:15,17 --> 1:28:17,305
l'm a grown man and l live with my mama!


1028
1:28:17,305 --> 1:28:23,411
l can't get a damn job!
You think l wanna be here?


1029
1:28:23,411 --> 1:28:25,8
This is it.


1030
1:28:25,8 --> 1:28:28,383
This is bullshit! All of it, it's bullshit!


1031
1:28:28,383 --> 1:28:32,721
Wait a minute.


1032
1:28:32,721 --> 1:28:37,826
''Bullshit?''


1033
1:28:37,826 --> 1:28:39,16
This...


1034
1:28:39,16 --> 1:28:43,932
...what you just did, is bullshit.


1035
1:28:43,932 --> 1:28:47,936
This is who you are.


1036
1:28:47,936 --> 1:28:50,171
This is what you accomplished.


1037
1:28:50,171 --> 1:28:56,578
Now, you go and get what's yours.


1038
1:28:56,578 --> 1:28:59,514
You're a man.


1039
1:28:59,514 --> 1:29:1,95
A man like who?


1040
1:29:1,95 --> 1:29:4,452
Who you trying to be like, baby?


1041
1:29:4,452 --> 1:29:6,421
Like your father?


1042
1:29:6,421 --> 1:29:10,91
l'm not gonna let you be the man
your father was.


1043
1:29:10,91 --> 1:29:13,361
l don't need another dead man.


1044
1:29:13,361 --> 1:29:17,866
l am not gonna have you
give up and die on me, too, goddammit.


1045
1:29:17,866 --> 1:29:22,971
l am not going to let you die.


1046
1:29:22,971 --> 1:29:26,875
This is what we're gonna do.


1047
1:29:26,875 --> 1:29:29,644
Now...


1048
1:29:29,644 --> 1:29:35,717
...you're gonna go down there
to them employment people again.


1049
1:29:35,717 --> 1:29:38,953
You're gonna look them in the eye...


1050
1:29:38,953 --> 1:29:42,357
...and you're gonna tell them the truth.


1051
1:29:42,357 --> 1:29:44,526
Step up, baby...


1052
1:29:44,526 --> 1:29:48,296
...and tell them who you are.


1053
1:29:48,296 --> 1:29:50,965
You are Greg Yance...


1054
1:29:50,965 --> 1:29:58,239
...and you are not going to die.


1055
1:29:58,239 --> 1:30:2,444
Can l tell you about
my experience down there?


1056
1:30:2,444 --> 1:30:4,879
l worked 18 hours a day...


1057
1:30:4,879 --> 1:30:6,548
...for $3 a week.


1058
1:30:6,548 --> 1:30:10,151
Throwing sandbags from dawn to dusk.


1059
1:30:10,151 --> 1:30:15,256
Stepping in water with snakes
and all types of insects l never seen before.


1060
1:30:15,256 --> 1:30:17,659
We worked in 110-degree heat.


1061
1:30:17,659 --> 1:30:20,628
Uniform soaked.


1062
1:30:20,628 --> 1:30:24,566
Feet blistered, hands raw,
mosquito bites all over my body.


1063
1:30:24,566 --> 1:30:29,437
After we finished, we'd still have to do
our P.T., that's physical training.


1064
1:30:29,437 --> 1:30:33,274
Stomach crunches and pushups
and jumping jacks.


1065
1:30:33,274 --> 1:30:36,878
Then we'd still have to jog
three miles a day.


1066
1:30:36,878 --> 1:30:40,815
l know that may sound like
a nightmare to you, but....


1067
1:30:40,815 --> 1:30:45,72
Throwing sandbags on that levee
was the best job l've ever had.


1068
1:30:45,72 --> 1:30:49,57
The people there...


1069
1:30:49,57 --> 1:30:51,826
